# validate-guidance-obligations wiring rule

Run `signalos validate-guidance-obligations` when product-agent work is created,
reviewed, or handed off.

- Missing required guidance is a blocker.
- The validator must use the same stack/action context as the agent packet.
- `--loaded` should point at the guidance material actually presented to the
  agent whenever that evidence exists.
- Do not mark guidance compliance from catalog presence alone; validate the
  loaded packet against touched paths.
